I was maybe around 3 years old. I was in the park with my parents and my dad had helped me climb up a tree that was near the edge of the park. It was winter and I was wearing an ushanka hat, the hat with the big floppy ears. For some reason this park had anti climb fences around all the edges of the park, the tall ass fences with spikes or barbed wire on top. My mum was getting ready to take a pic of me in the tree when a bird flew right in my face and scared me. I fell backwards and can remember almost getting stabbed right in the head by the fence. My hat got caught on the top of fence and I cut myself behind my ear. My first memory and it is why I am scared of heights. There is also another memory from around the same time when i was also going to the park and I was on my scooter and I rode directly into a push and was stung in the eye/near the eye by a bee or wasp, can't remember that well. And yes, I am scared of bees/wasps too.
